dict.string:
“Have a Panic Attack!” by Jackie Arko
 
Uh oh! You’re alive and awake. You know what that means: a panic attack is just a stimulus away! 

Maybe you just said something embarrassing. Maybe you’re newly convinced that you drank spoiled milk and now you’re on the highway to botulism. Perhaps you felt a “weird” feeling in your right ring finger and it’s because you’re having a heart attack – a secret heart attack that has no symptoms but will instantly kill you. Did you know that most people don’t even know when they’re having a heart attack? Their friends are all, “You should go to the ER” and they say, “Nah, I’m fine,” and then BOOM, they’re fucking DEAD! Did you know that happens every half second in the United States? It’s happening to someone RIGHT NOW. Why couldn’t it – why shouldn’t it – be you? You fit the profile perfectly – a healthy 29 year old with no family history of heart disease. OH MY GOD YOU ARE HAVING A FUCKING HEART ATTACK.

Do something! Save yourself! Click on the various items you have at your disposal and stave off this panic attack! Be careful, though – you never know what could end up making it worse. Keep a watchful eye on your panic meter - if it reaches 100% it's game over.  If you can coax it down to 0% you're safe… at least for a few minutes.




Illustration by Anthony Montuori     Gamification by Brian Perry

Cat
[increase panic by 30%]

NOPE. There are two main things wrong with seeking solace from a cat. First of all, your cat does not love you. At best, she views you as an enjoyable utility that she can take advantage of as she pleases. If your cat senses you’re upset, she’s going to walk the fuck away so that she doesn’t have to deal with your nerdy histrionics.  Also, when you tried to pick up and cuddle your cat for comfort just now, she clawed and/or bit you, and do you even know how likely it is for a cat scratch or bite that breaks the skin to get infected? It’s like 80%. So now you have to go to the bathroom and wash your wound repeatedly and put antibiotic ointment on it and check in obsessively every 5 minutes to see if it’s swelling.

Television
[reduce panic by 20%]

So this is conditional on what you choose to watch, but since you know yourself and what will set you off, it’s safe to assume you won’t put on something that will make everything worse, like a medical show, or something with people dying, or something involving a lot of chase scenes or suspense or anger or failure or anything that could cause you to self-reflect. You need something that’s a jaunty black hole of media.

Chamomile Tea
[increase panic by 15%]

This one is tricky. Some people can drink Chamomile and feel like it’s just regular tea. Others feel tired and lethargic after they drink it… but not tired or lethargic enough. Chamomile might be able to stave off a panic attack if it hasn’t started yet, but you’re too deep into this nightmare to have some wimpy-ass tea to pull you out of it. The mild drowsiness is no match for your racing heart rate and sweaty palms, and in fact, it’s making everything worse because you haven’t zonked yourself out enough to feel relief, but merely compromised. Your guard is down, and you know what THAT means – that’s when you die.

Significant Other
[reduce panic by 20%]

Chances are, your significant other knows how fucking crazy you are and lands somewhere on the scale of “it hurts me to see you hurting and I want to comfort you and take care of you” to “you’re batshit sometimes, but you make up for it by being real good at oral.” Regardless of where they fall on that spectrum, they’re going to comfort you for one reason or another. Bonus points if they actually know how to comfort you in that perfect way so that everything almost immediately gets better. Seriously, get married to that motherfucker now because that shit is rare. However, even if you get a half-grunt of, “Don’t be ridiculous, you don’t have cancer in your ear,” from behind a laptop, it’s still a person telling you that having cancer in your ear is ridiculous, and that’s worth something.

Book 
[increase panic by 20%]

So it depends on what kind of book we’re talking about, but if it’s anything worth reading, it’s not going to cut it. You need to turn your brain off, not feed it. If this is a halfway decent book, it requires you to be able to sit quietly and absorb it and contemplate it and appreciate it, and that’s impossible when you’re having a pulmonary embolism.

Couch 
[reduce panic by 20%]

Good move. Sit the fuck down. There is nothing worse than standing while panic is creeping up on you. You’ll inevitably start pacing, and then hyperventilating, which will cause you to pass out and most likely die. So sit. The fuck. Down.

Computer 
[increase panic by 50%]

Are you fucking kidding me?! Do you even know what lives on your computer? The Internet. You know what’s totes easily-accessible on the Internet? WebMD.  Sure, you could just use your computer to watch funny shit on Hulu, but you know damn well that you don’t have the self control to stop yourself from WedMD-ing “stiff neck” and concluding that you have a rare and deadly strain of meningitis.

Whiskey 
[reduce panic by 5%]

Yeah, okay, you could drink yourself into oblivion, sure. BUT, you’re terrified of becoming an alcoholic. You’re actually continually shocked that you’re NOT an alcoholic. That shit sneaks up on people, and when you combine that with being acutely aware of your mortality every single goddamn day since you were 12, it’s a recipe for self-medicating. Better limit it to two shots. Less chance of hysterical tears and self-loathing.

Marijuana 
[increase panic by 20%]

Oh sure, yeah, okay. You’re thinking. “I’ll smoke some weed, mellow out a bit.” Here’s the thing, though – you’re past the line where this helps because you’re already panicking. Smoke this and you will be gripping the edge of a table, feeling like your heart is going to blow out of your chest like in Alien.

US Weekly
[reduce panic by 20%]

Yep – good move. Every time you read one of these you erase a part of your brain, which is what’s causing the problem in the first place. Crack that thing open and absorb every last word. Britney Spears has a new boy toy? Miley Cyrus is addicted to coke? Cher is dating a 15 year old? Now you see that your life could be so much more absurd.

Dog 
[reduce panic by 30%]

Well done. Dogs are the best. Your dog loves the shit out of you, and he can tell that you’re upset, and he is feeling the need to protect you as a result. You can feel that energy, and if you look right into your dog’s eyes you will hear him thinking, “Everything is going to be okay.” There is some Cesar Milan shit happening between you and your dog right now.

UH OH – YOU HAD A PANIC ATTACK
 

Better rush off to the emergency room and tell the doctor on call that you’re dying. Embarrassing? Yes, but YOU’RE DYING. There’s NO TIME TO GIVE A FUCK ABOUT “EMBARRASSING.” WOULD YOU RATHER BE EMBARRASSED OR FUCKING DEAD? OK… OK YOU’RE JUST GOING TO GET YOUR COAT ON AND… WHERE THE FUCK ARE YOUR KEYS?! SHOULD YOU CALL 911?? Ugh, ambulances are SO EXPENSIVE. No… no you can just drive yourself… stop crying and hyperventilating at the same time or you’re going to have an aneurysm. Oh god… is that… why is there that sharp pain in your temple??? IS THAT THE ANEURYSM THAT’S BEEN LURKING AROUND THE CORNER FOR THE LAST 30 YEARS OF YOUR LIFE, like a TICKING TIME BOMB? At the very least you’re going to get into a car accident on the way to the hospit… JESUS CHRIST, WHAT IF YOU GET IN A CAR ACCIDENT ON THE WAY TO THE HOSPITAL?

Enough Already.
Time to stop fucking around.
           > > > > >

Xanax
[gain a ton of panic, then gain even more calm]

You know your panic attack is going to get worse immediately after taking this, because you’re giving up and dropping your guard and if someone breaks into your house while you’re on Xanax you’re not going to be able to carry out your emergency defense plan as efficiently as you would like to. However, desperate times call for desperate measures, so good for you! You made it through that agonizing first 3 minutes post-pill-popping and you’re on your way to genuinely laughing at that Adam Sandler movie and then passing out cold for 6 hours, waking up in a puddle of your own drool and not remembering what day it is. Congratulations on figuring out life!

WAY TO GO – YOU CALMED THE FUCK DOWN

Well done, you! Thanks to the magic of pharmaceuticals and stupefying media, you’re functioning again. Go order a Life is Good t-shirt online or something. Don’t push it by leaving the house or anything like that, but you’ll probably be okay. At least until you feel that tumor in your forearm and are convinced you have lymphoma.
